abstract: The president frequently injects his own words into statements he claims his supporters said on Fox News or elsewhere. They rarely publicly correct him.
snippet: The president frequently injects his own words into statements he claims his supporters said on Fox News or elsewhere. They rarely publicly correct him.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Watching Fox News ahead of Wednesday’s impeachment vote, President Trump gave a Twitter call out to one of his most combative allies in the House.

abstract: The messaging system that he and a friend created in 1978 was a forerunner of social media services like Twitter, Facebook and YouTube.
snippet: The messaging system that he and a friend created in 1978 was a forerunner of social media services like Twitter, Facebook and YouTube.
lead_paragraph: Randy Suess, a computer hobbyist who helped build the first online bulletin board, anticipating the rise of the internet, messaging apps and social media, died on Dec. 10 at a hospital in Chicago. He was 74.

abstract: The White Sox boosted their starting rotation, finalizing a $5 million, one-year contract with two-time All-Star Gio González that includes a 2021 club option.
snippet: The White Sox boosted their starting rotation, finalizing a $5 million, one-year contract with two-time All-Star Gio González that includes a 2021 club option.
lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — The White Sox boosted their starting rotation, finalizing a $5 million, one-year contract with two-time All-Star Gio González that includes a 2021 club option.
headline_main: White Sox Boost Rotation, Agree to $5M Deal With Gonzalez
headline_print_headline: White Sox Boost Rotation, Agree to $5M Deal With Gonzalez

abstract: The son of a Russian spy couple who lived clandestine lives in Canada and the United States said Friday that he wants a future in Canada after the country's Supreme Court ruled he can keep his Canadian citizenship.
snippet: The son of a Russian spy couple who lived clandestine lives in Canada and the United States said Friday that he wants a future in Canada after the country's Supreme Court ruled he can keep his Canadian citizenship.
lead_paragraph: TORONTO — The son of a Russian spy couple who lived clandestine lives in Canada and the United States said Friday that he wants a future in Canada after the country's Supreme Court ruled he can keep his Canadian citizenship.
headline_main: Son of Russian Spies Relieved to Keep Canadian Citizenship
headline_print_headline: Son of Russian Spies Relieved to Keep Canadian Citizenship

abstract: It used to be easy for the International Brotherhood of Real Bearded Santas to know who could become a member. No more.
snippet: It used to be easy for the International Brotherhood of Real Bearded Santas to know who could become a member. No more.
lead_paragraph: For years, there wasn’t much confusion about who could join the International Brotherhood of Real Bearded Santas, the largest membership organization of Santas in the world. It was open only to men with whiskers long enough to be styled like St. Nick’s, which could withstand a firm tug from a formidable toddler.

abstract: Many of Canada's drug suppliers cannot, or will not, agree to ship cheaper prescription medicines into the United States, a new challenge to the Trump administration's push to reduce drug prices, companies and industry officials told Reuters.

lead_paragraph: TORONTO — Many of Canada's drug suppliers cannot, or will not, agree to ship cheaper prescription medicines into the United States, a new challenge to the Trump administration's push to reduce drug prices, companies and industry officials told Reuters.

abstract: Enrollments for 2020 insurance plans, under the Affordable Care Act (ACA), on the HealthCare.gov website fell by about 200,000 from last year to 8.3 million, the U.S. government said on Friday, citing preliminary data.

abstract: Sutter Health [SHLC.UL], which runs hospitals and clinics in northern California, has agreed to pay $575 million to settle allegations that it engaged in anticompetitive practices, the California attorney general's office said on Friday.

abstract: The economic impact of Boeing Co's planned halt of 737 MAX production will not be considered by U.S. regulators in their ongoing review of when to end the grounding of a plane involved in two major fatal crashes, U.S. Transportation Secretary Elaine Chao said on Friday.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The economic impact of Boeing Co's planned halt of 737 MAX production will not be considered by U.S. regulators in their ongoing review of when to end the grounding of a plane involved in two major fatal crashes, U.S. Transportation Secretary Elaine Chao said on Friday.
headline_main: U.S. Transport Chief Said Economic Issues Not a Factor in 737 MAX's Safety Review
